Event: Vacuum Tube (Fleming) - Enabled electronic switching for computing
Turing Machine (Alan Turing) - Defined computability limits
Shannon's Thesis - Boolean logic to electrical circuits (birth of the bit)
ENIAC - First programmable electronic general-purpose computer
Transistor (Bell Labs) - Solid-state replacement for tubes
Turing's "Computing Machinery and Intelligence" - Turing Test proposed
Dartmouth Conference - "Artificial Intelligence" term coined; birth of AI field
Perceptron (Rosenblatt) - Early neural network hardware
Integrated Circuit (Kilby) - Multiple transistors on one chip
Arthur Samuel coins "Machine Learning"; self-improving checkers program
Moore's Law stated (Gordon Moore) - Transistor doubling prediction
ARPANET - Precursor to Internet; Shakey the Robot (first mobile planner)
Intel 4004 - First commercial microprocessor
First AI Winter begins (~1973-1980) - Funding cuts after overhype
Backpropagation revival (Rumelhart/Hinton) - Enabled multi-layer neural nets
Second AI Winter (~1987-1993) - Expert systems collapse
Deep Blue (IBM) - Brute-force chess victory over Kasparov
Honda ASIMO - Advanced humanoid walking (rule-based)
Roomba (iRobot) - First mass-market autonomous home robot
Hinton et al. rebrand "Deep Learning"; deep belief networks
AWS launch - Cloud computing infrastructure for scale
NVIDIA CUDA - GPUs enabled for general-purpose parallel computing
ImageNet dataset (Fei-Fei Li) - 14M+ labeled images fuel vision models
DeepMind founded - Goal to solve intelligence
IBM Watson wins Jeopardy!; Siri launches (Apple)
AlexNet - CNN crushes ImageNet; deep learning breakthrough
Google Cat Paper - Unsupervised learning from YouTube videos
Word2Vec (Google) - Semantic word embeddings
DeepMind DQN - Atari games from pixels (reinforcement learning)
GANs invented (Ian Goodfellow) - Generative adversarial networks
OpenAI founded; TensorFlow open-sourced; ResNet (very deep nets)
AlphaGo (DeepMind) - Defeats Lee Sedol in Go
Transformers paper ("Attention Is All You Need")
GPT-1 (OpenAI); BERT (Google) - Transformer NLP advances
GPT-2 (OpenAI) - Emergent scaling behaviors
GPT-3 (OpenAI) - 175B params; few-shot learning
AlphaFold (DeepMind) - Protein structure prediction breakthrough
DALL-E (OpenAI) - Text-to-image generation; Codex (early coding)
ChatGPT (based on GPT-3.5) - Mass adoption of conversational AI
Stable Diffusion - Open-source diffusion model revolution
GPT-4 (OpenAI) - Multimodal; major capability jump
Gemini 1.0 (Google); Grok-1 (xAI); Llama 2 (Meta open weights)
Sora (OpenAI video gen); Claude 3 family (Anthropic); o1 reasoning model
Gemini 1.5/2.0; Llama 3.1 405B (Meta); EU AI Act
Grok-3 (xAI) - Frontier reasoning model
o3 / Claude 4 family advances; Gemini 2.5/3; agentic tools scale (Devin etc.)
Quantum error-correction milestones (e.g. Willow-like chips)
Agentic AI & recursive self-improvement loops emerge at scale
Tesla Optimus production pivot; world models (Genie-like)
Omni-modal single models; recursive learning + infinite context
